      "category": "Concrete",
      "subcategory": "Notes",
      "activityName": "Concrete Placement Notes",
      "description": "This figure provides man-hours for labor and equipment to place and vibrate concrete. For upper stories, add per story: placed by pump, use a 1.07 multiplier; placed by bucket or crane, use a 1.05 multiplier. Construction that moves in and out of ramps, runways, or staging is not included. For moving in and out, use 0.22 man-hours per linear foot. Major considerations in planning concrete placement are: method of placement, accessibility, rate of placement in regard to form design, amount and frequency of delivery governed by the ability to screed, tamp, and finish.",
